<p><strong>Additional SPIN intern accomplishments include</strong>:</p>
<ul><li>Arumugam and Eustis also participated in the Ashby Prize in Computa=
tional Science hackathon at the University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign, <a=
 href=3D"https://ai.ncsa.illinois.edu/news-events/2022/05/center-for-ai-inn=
ovation-announces-hackathon-winners/">placing second and third</a>, respect=
ively.</li><li>Ravi received <a href=3D"https://blogs.illinois.edu/view/620=
4/678500770">recognition</a> for his oral presentation at the 2022 Undergra=
duate Research Symposium.</li><li>Foziea Garada gave a talk about her Nobel=
 Project at the NCSA All-Staff meeting in April.</li><li>Eustis took home <=
a href=3D"https://ai.ncsa.illinois.edu/news-events/2022/04/caii-students-wi=
ns-treehacks2022/">two prizes</a> at TreeHacks 2022 at Stanford University.=
 Eustis won the =E2=80=9CBest ML Hack=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CMost likely to =
Become a Business=E2=80=9D prizes for his project on Machine Learning effic=
iency called =E2=80=9CFine Tuned Heads.=E2=80=9D<ul><li>=E2=80=9CI am extre=
mely thankful to have won the (TreeHacks 2022) prizes,=E2=80=9D Eustis said=
. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m also thankful to NCSA. NCSA=E2=80=99s SPIN program h=
as allowed me to develop my passion for efficient ML.=E2=80=9D</li></ul></l=
i></ul>
<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><strong>Virtual Poster Presentations</strong=
></h2>
<p>Check out these <a href=3D"https://www.ncsa.illinois.edu/spin-virtual-po=
ster-session-2021-22/">engaging poster presentations</a> from the 2021-22 S=
PIN interns to learn more about the projects and research they=E2=80=99re w=
orking on at our center. These videos will be available for viewing until J=
une 3.</p>
<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><strong>Interns and Mentors Nominated for Re=
cognition</strong></h2>
<p>Congratulations to all SPIN interns, mentors and recent Illinois graduat=
